<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-581-681  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 581 681.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  May 10 1989 n1173* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple sets 32-bit working, virtual memory, multi-tasking for MacOS. (future releases of System Software for the Macintosh )andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (product development).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentSoftware PackagesEnhancementsVirtual Memory32-BitMultitasking.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>APPLE SETS 32-BIT WORKING, VIRTUAL MEMORY, MULTI-TASKINGandM;FOR MAC OSandM;Apple Computer Inc this week discussed future releases of theandM;System Software for the Macintosh, saying that it planned to add virtualmemory support, 32-bit addressing, and a new Interapplication CommunicationsArchitecture for multi-tasking.andP;  IAC is described as an integratedcommunications framework that  enables applications to exchange data andinstructions either on a single Mac or over a network, and includes both thefoundation software to facilitate communications and common protocols thatenable applications to interact in a consistent manner.andP;  New imaging systemsoftware is being designed to maximise Mac capabilities in the areas ofcolour, text and printing, and includes outline fonts, a new Layout Managerarchitecture for printing and the previously introduced 32-Bit QuickDrawsoftware.andP;  The Outline fonts are mathematical descriptions of text that canbe scaled to any point size at any resolution, providing sharp text ondisplays, printers, fax modems and other output devices.andP;  All will be inSystem 7.0 of the Mac software, planned for availability later in the year.andO;</TEXT></DOC>